<statement>
<image width="33%"  pi:generated="problems/images/61e8e8b2d235158a4fecaad9e0d52728.png" /><p>
Suppose a = 10 and A = 20 degrees. Calculate:</p>
<p>
b = <fillin characters="20" /></p>
<p>
c = <fillin characters="20" /></p>
<p>
B = <fillin characters="20" /> degrees</p>
<p>
Round all answers to one decimal place.  Give angles in <em>degrees</em>
</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>27.5</li><li>29.2</li><li>70.0</li></ul></p><p>First calculate the length of the other leg.</p>
<p>For the length of the other leg,</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\tan{{\left({20}\right)}}}=\frac{{10}}{{b}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{b}=\frac{{10}}{{\tan{{\left({20}\right)}}}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{b}\approx{27.474774194546}\approx{27.5}</m>.</p>
<p>For the third side</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={10}^{{2}}+{27.474774194546}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={100}+{754.8632170413}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={854.8632170413}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}=\sqrt{{{854.8632170413}}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}\approx{29.238044001631}\approx{29.2}</m>.</p>
<p>For angle B</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{B}={180}^{\circ}-{90}^{\circ}-{20}^{\circ}\approx{70}^{\circ}</m></p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

